quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,70,"Or do they say, "
  23,71,"But if the Truth [i.e., Allāh] had followed their inclinations, the heavens and the earth and whoever is in them would have been ruined. Rather, We have brought them their message,{1} but they, from their message, are turning away.",footnotes:1:Or "reminder."
  23,72,"Or do you, [O Muḥammad], ask them for payment? But the reward of your Lord is best, and He is the best of providers."
  24,52,"And whoever obeys Allāh and His Messenger and fears Allāh and is conscious of Him - it is those who are the attainers."
  24,53,"And they swear by Allāh their strongest oaths that if you ordered them, they would go forth [in Allāh's cause]. Say, ",footnotes:1:i.e., the hypocrites' pretense of obedience is known to be a lie.
  24,54,"Say, "
  25,16,"For them therein is whatever they wish, [while] abiding eternally. It is ever upon your Lord a promise [worthy to be] requested.{1}",footnotes:1:Or "...a promise requested [for them by the angels]."
  25,17,"And [mention] the Day He will gather them and that which they worship besides Allāh and will say, "
  25,18,"They will say, "